.ie \n(.g .ds Aq \(aq
.el .ds Aq '
.TH f00 1  "f00 0.5.0" 
.SH NAME
f00 \- List directory contents with a friendly default UI
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBf00\fR [\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-a\fR|\fB\-\-all\fR] [\fB\-A\fR|\fB\-\-almost\-all\fR] [\fB\-l \fR] [\fB\-1 \fR] [\fB\-C \fR] [\fB\-m \fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-human\-readable\fR] [\fB\-\-si\fR] [\fB\-R\fR|\fB\-\-recursive\fR] [\fB\-r\fR|\fB\-\-reverse\fR] [\fB\-t \fR] [\fB\-S \fR] [\fB\-X \fR] [\fB\-v \fR] [\fB\-U \fR] [\fB\-\-sort\fR] [\fB\-\-time\fR] [\fB\-u \fR] [\fB\-c \fR] [\fB\-\-color\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-csv\fR] [\fB\-\-tsv\fR] [\fB\-\-tree\fR] [\fB\-\-gnu\fR] [\fB\-\-icons\fR] [\fB\-F\fR|\fB\-\-classify\fR] [\fB\-p \fR] [\fB\-\-file\-type\fR] [\fB\-\-indicator\-style\fR] [\fB\-\-group\-directories\-first\fR] [\fB\-d\fR|\fB\-\-directory\fR] [\fB\-B\fR|\fB\-\-ignore\-backups\fR] [\fB\-I\fR|\fB\-\-ignore\fR] [\fB\-\-hide\fR] [\fB\-L\fR|\fB\-\-dereference\fR] [\fB\-H\fR|\fB\-\-dereference\-command\-line\fR] [\fB\-\-dereference\-command\-line\-symlink\-to\-dir\fR] [\fB\-g \fR] [\fB\-o \fR] [\fB\-G\fR|\fB\-\-no\-group\fR] [\fB\-n\fR|\fB\-\-numeric\-uid\-gid\fR] [\fB\-i\fR|\fB\-\-inode\fR] [\fB\-s\fR|\fB\-\-size\fR] [\fB\-k\fR|\fB\-\-kibibytes\fR] [\fB\-\-block\-size\fR] [\fB\-\-full\-time\fR] [\fB\-\-time\-style\fR] [\fB\-q\fR|\fB\-\-hide\-control\-chars\fR] [\fB\-\-show\-control\-chars\fR] [\fB\-b\fR|\fB\-\-escape\fR] [\fB\-Q\fR|\fB\-\-quote\-name\fR] [\fB\-N\fR|\fB\-\-literal\fR] [\fB\-\-quoting\-style\fR] [\fB\-x \fR] [\fB\-f \fR] [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-T\fR|\fB\-\-tabsize\fR] [\fB\-w\fR|\fB\-\-width\fR] [\fB\-Z\fR|\fB\-\-context\fR] [\fB\-\-zero\fR] [\fB\-D\fR|\fB\-\-dired\fR] [\fB\-\-author\fR] [\fB\-\-hyperlink\fR] [\fB\-\-max\-depth\fR] [\fB\-\-git\fR] [\fB\-\-config\fR] [\fB\-\-browse\fR] [\fB\-\-ignore\-files\fR] [\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR] [\fB\-\-archive\fR] [\fB\-\-threads\fR] [\fB\-\-profile\fR] [\fB\-\-update\fR] [\fB\-\-check\-update\fR] [\fB\-\-list\-plugins\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIPATHS\fR] 
.SH DESCRIPTION
List directory contents with a friendly default UI
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR
Print help
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
Do not ignore entries starting with `.`
.TP
\fB\-A\fR, \fB\-\-almost\-all\fR
Do not list implied `.` and `..` (show other hidden files)
.TP
\fB\-l\fR
Use a long listing format
.TP
\fB\-1\fR
List one file per line
.TP
\fB\-C\fR
List entries by columns
.TP
\fB\-m\fR
Fill width with a comma separated list of entries
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-human\-readable\fR
With \-l and \-s, print sizes like 1K 234M 2G etc
.TP
\fB\-\-si\fR
Likewise, but use powers of 1000 not 1024
.TP
\fB\-R\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
List subdirectories recursively
.TP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-reverse\fR
Reverse sort order
.TP
\fB\-t\fR
Sort by time, newest first
.TP
\fB\-S\fR
Sort by file size, largest first
.TP
\fB\-X\fR
Sort alphabetically by entry extension
.TP
\fB\-v\fR
Natural sort of (version) numbers within text (`strverscmp`)
.TP
\fB\-U\fR
Do not sort; list entries in directory order
.TP
\fB\-\-sort\fR \fI<WORD>\fR
Sort by WORD (name, size, time, extension, version, none)
.TP
\fB\-\-time\fR \fI<WORD>\fR
Use time WORD for display/sort: mtime, atime, ctime, birth
.TP
\fB\-u\fR
Sort by, and show, access time
.TP
\fB\-c\fR
Sort by, and show, ctime (status change) when possible
.TP
\fB\-\-color\fR[=\fI<WHEN>\fR] [default: auto]
Colorize output
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit structured JSON
.TP
\fB\-\-csv\fR
Emit CSV
.TP
\fB\-\-tsv\fR
Emit TSV
.TP
\fB\-\-tree\fR
Show entries as a tree
.TP
\fB\-\-gnu\fR
Stricter GNU ls\-compatible behavior
.TP
\fB\-\-icons\fR[=\fI<WHEN>\fR] [default: auto]
Show file icons (auto/always/never; default: auto — TTY only, off under \-\-gnu)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
auto
.IP \(bu 2
always
.IP \(bu 2
never
.RE
.TP
\fB\-F\fR, \fB\-\-classify\fR
Append indicator (one of */=@|) to entries
.TP
\fB\-p\fR
Append / indicator to directories
.TP
\fB\-\-file\-type\fR
Like \-F, except do not append \*(Aq*\*(Aq
.TP
\fB\-\-indicator\-style\fR \fI<WORD>\fR
Append indicator with style WORD: none, slash, file\-type, classify
.TP
\fB\-\-group\-directories\-first\fR
Group directories before files
.TP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-directory\fR
List directories themselves, not their contents
.TP
\fB\-B\fR, \fB\-\-ignore\-backups\fR
Do not list implied entries ending with ~
.TP
\fB\-I\fR, \fB\-\-ignore\fR \fI<PATTERN>\fR
Do not list implied entries matching shell PATTERN (repeatable)
.TP
\fB\-\-hide\fR \fI<PATTERN>\fR
Do not list implied entries matching shell PATTERN (unless \-a/\-A)
.TP
\fB\-L\fR, \fB\-\-dereference\fR
When showing file information for a symbolic link, show info for the file it references
.TP
\fB\-H\fR, \fB\-\-dereference\-command\-line\fR
Follow symbolic links listed on the command line
.TP
\fB\-\-dereference\-command\-line\-symlink\-to\-dir\fR
Follow each command line symbolic link that points to a directory
.TP
\fB\-g\fR
Like \-l, but do not list owner
.TP
\fB\-o\fR
Like \-l, but do not list group information
.TP
\fB\-G\fR, \fB\-\-no\-group\fR
In a long listing, don\*(Aqt print group names
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-numeric\-uid\-gid\fR
Like \-l, but list numeric user and group IDs
.TP
\fB\-i\fR, \fB\-\-inode\fR
Print the index number of each file
.TP
\fB\-s\fR, \fB\-\-size\fR
Print the allocated size of each file, in blocks
.TP
\fB\-k\fR, \fB\-\-kibibytes\fR
Default to 1024\-byte blocks for filesystem disk usage (`\-s`)
.TP
\fB\-\-block\-size\fR \fI<SIZE>\fR
Scale sizes by SIZE before printing (e.g. 1K, 1M, KB, MB)
.TP
\fB\-\-full\-time\fR
Like \-l \-\-time\-style=full\-iso
.TP
\fB\-\-time\-style\fR \fI<TIME_STYLE>\fR
Time/date format with \-l; also TIME_STYLE env
.TP
\fB\-q\fR, \fB\-\-hide\-control\-chars\fR
Print ? instead of nongraphic characters
.TP
\fB\-\-show\-control\-chars\fR
Show nongraphic characters as\-is (the default unless \-q)
.TP
\fB\-b\fR, \fB\-\-escape\fR
Print C\-style escapes for nongraphic characters
.TP
\fB\-Q\fR, \fB\-\-quote\-name\fR
Enclose entry names in double quotes
.TP
\fB\-N\fR, \fB\-\-literal\fR
Print entry names without quoting
.TP
\fB\-\-quoting\-style\fR \fI<WORD>\fR
Use quoting style WORD for entry names
.TP
\fB\-x\fR
List entries by lines instead of by columns (row\-major)
.TP
\fB\-f\fR
Same as \-a \-U (and disable decorations in GNU mode)
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<WORD>\fR
Across/commas/long/single\-column/vertical
.TP
\fB\-T\fR, \fB\-\-tabsize\fR \fI<COLS>\fR
Assume tab stops at each COLS instead of 8 (stored for layout)
.TP
\fB\-w\fR, \fB\-\-width\fR \fI<COLS>\fR
Set output width to COLS; 0 means no limit
.TP
\fB\-Z\fR, \fB\-\-context\fR
Print any security context of each file (SELinux)
.TP
\fB\-\-zero\fR
End each output line with NUL, not newline
.TP
\fB\-D\fR, \fB\-\-dired\fR
Generate output designed for Emacs\*(Aq dired mode
.TP
\fB\-\-author\fR
With \-l, print the author of each file
.TP
\fB\-\-hyperlink\fR[=\fI<WHEN>\fR]
Hyperlink file names (auto/always/never)
.TP
\fB\-\-max\-depth\fR \fI<N>\fR
Maximum recursion depth (with \-R / \-\-tree)
.TP
\fB\-\-git\fR \fI<GIT>\fR [default: true]
Annotate with git status (requires feature `git`)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
true
.IP \(bu 2
false
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-config\fR \fI<PATH>\fR
Path to TOML config file (overrides default search path)
.TP
\fB\-\-browse\fR
Interactive TUI directory browser (requires feature `tui`)
.TP
\fB\-\-ignore\-files\fR
Honor `.gitignore` / `.f00ignore` when listing
.TP
\fB\-\-no\-ignore\fR
Do not honor ignore files (overrides \-\-ignore\-files)
.TP
\fB\-\-archive\fR \fI<ARCHIVE>\fR [default: true]
Auto\-list zip/tar archives as directories (default: true; off under \-\-gnu)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
true
.IP \(bu 2
false
.RE
.TP
\fB\-\-threads\fR \fI<N>\fR [default: 0]
Parallel metadata threads: `0` = auto (rayon default), `1` = serial, `N>1` = fixed pool
.TP
\fB\-\-profile\fR
Print phase timing breakdown to stderr (readdir/stat/sort/format/total)
.TP
\fB\-\-update\fR
Update f00 from the latest GitHub Release (checksum verified)
.TP
\fB\-\-check\-update\fR
Check whether a newer release is available (no mutation); exit 1 if behind
.TP
\fB\-\-list\-plugins\fR
List loaded plugins (requires feature `plugins`)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fIPATHS\fR]
Paths to list (default: current directory)
.SH VERSION
v0.5.0
